I"<p>Similar to the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/brain-is-like-hardware-mind-is-like-software">computational metaphor of cognition</a>, a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/attention-distorts-time">signal processing metaphor</a> of cognition might associate the brain with a carrier wave and the mind with the associated envelope. In signal processing, the carrier wave is a support mechanism which supports information to be expressed through envelope modulate, such as in AM or FM radio transmission.</p>
